1
00:00:01,602 --> 00:00:04,703
[ Clucking ]

2
00:00:05,872 --> 00:00:09,507
[ Broots ]
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
STOP, STOP!

3
00:00:09,576 --> 00:00:13,945
RIGHT HERE.
THIS IS IT.

4
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:22,220
<i> NICE JOB, BROOTS.</i>
<i> CAN YOU EVEN SPELL "MAP"?</i>

5
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:24,890
NO, WE'RE NOT LOST,
MISS PARKER. THE G.P.S.
COORDINATES JAROD GAVE US...

6
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:26,891
SAY IT'S RIGHT AROUND HERE.

7
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:31,863
ABOUT, UH, 25 YARDS...
THAT WAY!

8
00:00:36,637 --> 00:00:39,804
THIS SHOULD BE IT.
THIS-- THIS SHOULD BE IT,
RIGHT HERE.

9
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,541
THIS IS IT!
THIS IS IT!
ALL RIGHT!

10
00:00:42,610 --> 00:00:46,411
I'M WAY PAST THE POINT
OF LOSING PATIENCE
WITH JAROD'S LITTLE GAMES.

11
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:48,980
THIS IS A WASTE
OF TIME.

12
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,750
IF HE BROUGHT US HERE,
THERE MUST BE A REASON.

13
00:00:51,819 --> 00:00:55,286
YEAH. TO MAKE US FEEL
LIKE ASSES TRAIPSING
AROUND KANSAS ALL DAY.

14
00:00:55,356 --> 00:00:58,924
WELL, UH, ACTUALLY,
MISS PARKER, I DON'T THINK
WE'RE IN KANSAS ANYMORE.

15
00:00:58,992 --> 00:01:01,326
- WHAT'D YOU SAY?
- WELL, BASED ON THIS MAP,

16
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,562
WE JUST CROSSED THE STATE LINE
RIGHT THERE.

17
00:01:03,631 --> 00:01:05,897
NO. EXACTLY WHAT
DID YOU JUST SAY?

18
00:01:05,966 --> 00:01:08,266
I SAID, "I DON'T THINK
WE'RE IN KANSAS ANYMORE."

19
00:01:19,012 --> 00:01:21,613
WHAT'S THAT THERE?

20
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:30,021
A BRICK.
A YELLOW BRICK...
WITH AN ADDRESS ON IT.

21
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:32,924
- I GET IT.
FOLLOW THE YELLOW BRICK ROAD.
- VERY GOOD, BROOTS.

22
00:01:32,992 --> 00:01:35,793
I LOVE THAT STORY.
EITHER OF YOU MUNCHKINS...

23
00:01:35,862 --> 00:01:38,296
BREAK INTO SONG,
I'LL DROP A HOUSE ON YA.

24
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:44,936
LET'S GO FIND OUT WHAT OUR
LITTLE FLYING MONKEY IS UP TO.

25
00:01:52,512 --> 00:01:54,947
WELL, I SEE THAT
THE SLOP ON A SHINGLE...

26
00:01:55,015 --> 00:01:57,049
SEEMED TO WORK OUT ALL RIGHT
AFTER ALL.

27
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:00,551
I AM SORRY ABOUT
THE MISUNDERSTANDING.
BUT WITH THE NAME AND ALL, WELL,

28
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:03,588
I THOUGHT IT HAD SOMETHING TO DO
WITH THE BIOLOGICAL FUNCTION
OF A PIG.

29
00:02:03,657 --> 00:02:06,925
I'M JUST KINDA GLAD
THAT I DIDN'T SUGGEST
THE RED-EYED GRAVY.

30
00:02:06,994 --> 00:02:09,261
[ Laughing ]

31
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:11,329
OH. OH.

32
00:02:16,669 --> 00:02:19,971
- DO YOU HAVE A RESTROOM?
- FOR CUSTOMERS ONLY.

33
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:25,877
I'LL TAKE A DOUGHNUT.

34
00:02:58,445 --> 00:03:03,348
EXCUSE ME.
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?
YEAH. PEACHY.

35
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:06,985
-<i> I MEAN, IF THERE'S</i>
<i> SOMETHING I CAN DO?</i>
- DAMN IT!

36
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:19,063
THANKS.

37
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:35,747
-IT WAS JUST A KISS, SWEETHEART.
-MAYBE I CAN HELP YOU.

38
00:03:35,816 --> 00:03:38,550
- GETTING OUT OF THE WAY
WOULD BE A START.
- THAT GUY DIDN'T SEEM FRIENDLY.

39
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:42,487
YOU'RE A GREAT KISSER,
BUT IF YOU DON'T SHUT THE DOOR,
I'M GONNA HAVE TO HURT YOU.

40
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:44,823
SHUT THE DOOR!

41
00:03:46,293 --> 00:03:48,259
THERE. IT'S SHUT.

42
00:03:49,462 --> 00:03:51,829
[ Sighs ]
NOT WHAT I HAD IN MIND,

43
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:55,000
BUT WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GO WITH IT.

44
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:58,202
- [ Grunts ]
-<i> [ Horn Honking ]</i>

45
00:03:58,271 --> 00:04:01,005
<i> HE'S WEARING A BADGE.</i>
<i> YOU'RE ON THE RUN</i>
<i> FROM THE POLICE?</i>

46
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:04,776
NAH,<i> WE'RE</i> ON THE RUN
FROM THE POLICE. HOW'S IT FEEL
TO BE A WANTED MAN?

47
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:10,415
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

48
00:04:10,483 --> 00:04:12,417
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

49
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:16,354
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

50
00:04:16,423 --> 00:04:19,524
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

51
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:23,027
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

52
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:25,296
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

53
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:28,133
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

54
00:04:28,201 --> 00:04:30,202
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

55
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,370
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

56
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,938
LIFE'S A GIFT.

57
00:04:45,719 --> 00:04:48,219
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

58
00:04:57,364 --> 00:04:59,598
<i>YOU COULD HAVE TOLD ME YOU WERE</i>
<i>ON THE RUN FROM THE POLICE.</i>

59
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,633
I DON'T REMEMBER BEGGIN' YOU
TO GET IN THE CAR.

60
00:05:01,702 --> 00:05:03,668
I THOUGHT YOU NEEDED HELP.

61
00:05:03,737 --> 00:05:07,038
I APPRECIATE THE WHOLE DUDLEY
DO-RIGHT THING, BUT YOU'RE
A LITTLE OUT OF YOUR LEAGUE.

62
00:05:07,107 --> 00:05:09,674
WHAT ARE YOU?
INSURANCE, BANKER, WHAT?

63
00:05:09,743 --> 00:05:11,943
STOCK ANALYST.
AT LEAST I WAS.
UH-HUH.

64
00:05:12,012 --> 00:05:15,313
FAMILY MAN, TOO, I BET.
A COUPLE OF KIDS,
A PRETTY LITTLE WIFE.

65
00:05:15,382 --> 00:05:18,116
DRIVE 'EM TO SOCCER PRACTICE
IN THE S.U.V.

66
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:20,952
THE BEST THING YOU CAN DO
IS TURN YOURSELF IN.

67
00:05:21,021 --> 00:05:24,288
LOOK, YOU CAN RELAX, ALL RIGHT?
I'M NOT ON THE RUN
FROM THE COPS.

68
00:05:24,357 --> 00:05:27,425
I'M ON THE RUN FROM<i> A</i> COP.
SINGULAR.

69
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:30,996
THAT CHARMING GUY
BACK AT THE DINER WAS VINCE,
MY EX-BOYFRIEND.

70
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:32,998
HE'S NOT TAKIN' THE BREAKUP
REAL WELL.

71
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:35,200
YOU'RE TRYING TO TELL ME THAT
THAT COP WAS IN LOVE WITH YOU?

72
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:38,036
WHAT CAN I SAY?
I'M A HELL OF A CATCH.

73
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:45,142
WHERE ARE YOU HEADED?
NOWHERE. ANYWHERE.

74
00:05:45,212 --> 00:05:48,613
SOMEWHERE'S RIGHT UP THE ROAD.
DROP YOU OFF?

75
00:05:48,682 --> 00:05:51,983
I SUPPOSE WE'D PROBABLY
WIG OUT THE WIFE IF I
DROVE UP TO YOUR FRONT DOOR.

76
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:55,186
WELL, I DON'T HAVE A WIFE.
A HOME EITHER, FOR THAT MATTER.

77
00:05:57,724 --> 00:06:01,226
WHERE YOU HEADED?
NOWHERE.

78
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:04,028
ANYWHERE.
I ALREADY BEEN SOMEWHERE.

79
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:08,633
WELL, I'M GOING EAST,
SO I GUESS THAT'S
WHERE WE'RE HEADED.

80
00:06:09,737 --> 00:06:11,836
YOU CAN RIDE IF YOU WANT TO.

81
00:06:11,905 --> 00:06:14,739
IT MIGHT BE NICE IF I
KNEW YOUR NAME, THOUGH.

82
00:06:14,807 --> 00:06:19,077
JAROD.
NICE TO MEET YOU, JAROD.

83
00:06:19,146 --> 00:06:21,079
I'M ZOE.

84
00:06:32,492 --> 00:06:35,326
YOU'RE SURE THIS IS THE PLACE,
BROOTS?

85
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,496
WELL, THE ADDRESS
MATCHES THE BRICK.

86
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:41,332
IS IT ME, OR HAS OZ
BEEN SERIOUSLY REZONED?

87
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:43,534
<i>[ Distant Train Horn Blaring ]</i>

88
00:06:43,603 --> 00:06:48,173
- YEAH?
- HI. WE'RE LOOKING FOR...
WHO THE HELL KNOWS.

89
00:06:48,242 --> 00:06:51,876
- JAROD SENT US.
- OH. YOU MUST BE DOROTHY.

90
00:06:51,945 --> 00:06:55,180
-<i> HOLD ON A MINUTE.</i>
- IF SHE'S DOROTHY,

91
00:06:55,249 --> 00:06:58,250
THAT MAKES US, WHAT,
THE LION AND THE TIN MAN?

92
00:06:58,318 --> 00:07:01,118
YOU'RE TOTO AT BEST, BROOTS.

93
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:13,898
- HELLO?
- DOWN HERE.

94
00:07:15,702 --> 00:07:19,304
- DON'T TELL ME. YOU REPRESENT--
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

95
00:07:19,373 --> 00:07:22,540
JUST GET INSIDE
BEFORE I AIR-CONDITION
THE WHOLE DAMN WORLD.

96
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:25,977
I GUESS THE WIZARD FORGOT
TO PAY THE LIGHT BILL.

97
00:07:26,046 --> 00:07:29,881
HERE. HERE.

98
00:07:30,984 --> 00:07:32,984
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.

99
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:36,754
<i>FOLLOW, FOLLOW, FOLLOW, FOLLOW.</i>

100
00:07:36,823 --> 00:07:41,793
- IT JUST KEEPS GETTING BETTER.
-<i> [ Lock Clicking ]</i>

101
00:07:41,862 --> 00:07:45,730
- HEY! OPEN UP THE DOOR!
- NOT WITHOUT THE MAGIC WORDS!

102
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:49,401
<i> PARKER, I'M SURE</i>
<i> WE'LL GET OUT OF HERE</i>
<i> WHEN JAROD INTENDS US TO.</i>

103
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:53,471
[ Sighs ]
IF I ONLY HAD A BRAIN.
COME ON.

104
00:07:58,411 --> 00:08:00,945
[ Kids Chattering ]

105
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:10,822
-<i> LEMONADE, 50 CENTS.</i>
-<i> [ Zoe ] CHECK IT OUT.</i>

106
00:08:10,891 --> 00:08:15,460
- GOD, HOW MANY TIMES DID WE
DO THAT WHEN WE WERE KIDS?
- LEMONADE, 50 CENTS.

107
00:08:15,529 --> 00:08:18,930
- THEY'RE AWFULLY YOUNG
TO BE RUNNING A BUSINESS.
- IT'S A LEMONADE STAND.

108
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:21,866
ARE YOU TELLING ME YOU
AND YOUR FRIENDS NEVER DID THAT?

109
00:08:21,935 --> 00:08:25,636
EVERY KID DOES THAT.
NOT EVERY KID.

110
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:28,073
<i>LEMONADE.</i>

111
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:43,387
- HEY, GUYS. HOW'S BUSINESS?
- NOT SO GOOD.

112
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:45,656
MAYBE YOUR LUCK IS CHANGING.
MY FRIEND AND I HAVE BEEN
DRIVING FOR A WHILE,

113
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:47,658
AND WE'RE REALLY THIRSTY.

114
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:49,727
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, JAROD?
OH, YEAH.

115
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:52,130
WE'RE PARCHED.
HOW MUCH?

116
00:08:52,199 --> 00:08:54,532
FIFTY CENTS A GLASS.

117
00:08:54,601 --> 00:08:56,901
OH, WE'RE A LOT THIRSTIER
THAN THAT.

118
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:59,704
WE MIGHT NEED
THE WHOLE PITCHER.
MM-HMM.

119
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:05,210
YOU THINK THAT'LL COVER IT?

120
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:08,078
[ Girls ]
MOM!

121
00:09:08,147 --> 00:09:12,116
- MOTHER! MOM!
- TWO HUNDRED DOLLARS?

122
00:09:12,185 --> 00:09:15,019
I JUST REMEMBER WHEN MY
SISTER KATIE AND I
USED TO DO THIS.

123
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:19,223
WE'D START OUT DREAMIN' WE'D
MAKE A TON OF MONEY, AND, OF
COURSE, THAT WOULD NEVER HAPPEN.

124
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:22,493
I GUESS I
JUST WANTED TO SEE WHAT
A DREAM COME TRUE LOOKS LIKE.

125
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,562
SOUNDS LIKE YOU HAD
A GOOD CHILDHOOD.

126
00:09:24,631 --> 00:09:27,765
YEAH.
ABOUT A MILLION YEARS AGO.

127
00:09:28,801 --> 00:09:32,169
CHEERS.
CHEERS.

128
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:36,708
[ Coughs ]
OF COURSE, WHEN WE MADE IT,
WE ACTUALLY PUT SUGAR IN IT.

129
00:09:36,777 --> 00:09:38,943
MMM.
I THINK IT'S PERFECT.

130
00:09:41,948 --> 00:09:46,117
JAROD, YOU SCARE ME.

131
00:09:54,494 --> 00:09:57,194
- YOU COMIN'?
- YES.

132
00:09:57,263 --> 00:09:59,965
<i>♪ BUT IF YOU FEEL</i>
<i>  LIKE LOVIN' ME ♪</i>

133
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:03,134
<i>♪ AND YOU GOT THE NOTION ♪</i>

134
00:10:03,203 --> 00:10:06,571
[ Singing Along With Radio ]
♪ I SECOND THAT EMOTION ♪
SING IT!

135
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,707
♪ SO, IF YOU FEEL
LIKE GIVIN' ME ♪♪
I DON'T KNOW IT.

136
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:12,543
HEY, THERE'S A TAPE CASE
IN THE BACK.
♪♪ [ Off ]

137
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,412
GRAB SOMETHIN' THAT LOOKS GOOD.
YOU DON'T KNOW IT?

138
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:20,284
[ Laughs ]
♪ IF YOU FEEL LIKE LOVIN' ♪
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

139
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:23,321
THIS LOOKS INTERESTING.
YOU WANT TO TELL ME ABOUT IT?

140
00:10:23,389 --> 00:10:25,389
WHAT'S TO TELL?
I DON'T LIKE WRITIN' OUT CHECKS.

141
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,125
THAT'S NOT A CRIME, IS IT?
COME ON.
A BOX FULL OF CASH?

142
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:31,295
THAT COP BACK AT THE DINER?
I ALREADY TOLD YOU
ABOUT HIM.

143
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:33,331
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME THE TRUTH?
WHAT'D YOU DO, ROB A BANK?

144
00:10:41,274 --> 00:10:43,341
YOU KNOW, SCREW YOU, JAROD.
THE ONLY THING I'M GUILTY OF...

145
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:45,576
IS STAYING TOO LONG
IN A LOUSY RELATIONSHIP.

146
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:47,845
OH, WITH THE COP, RIGHT?
THAT'S RIGHT.

147
00:10:47,914 --> 00:10:50,181
EXCEPT VINCE DIDN'T KNOW HOW
TO LEAVE THE AUTHORITY FIGURE
THING AT HOME,

148
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:53,084
SO FOR TWO YEARS,
I PUT UP WITH HIM
BEATIN' THE CRAP OUT OF ME.

149
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:56,420
IT MIGHT BE TWO YEARS TOO LATE,
BUT AT LEAST I FINALLY
WALKED OUT.

150
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:59,190
THIS IS EVERY BIT
OF SAVINGS I HAD.

151
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:01,392
[ Sighs ]

152
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:03,928
SO THERE.
THAT'S MY HAPPY LITTLE TALE.

153
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:06,497
I'M 30 YEARS OLD,
AND MY WHOLE LIFE
IS TWO SUITCASES,

154
00:11:06,566 --> 00:11:09,901
$27,000 AND A '62 FORD.

155
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:12,203
I KINDA MISSED OUT
ON HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

156
00:11:13,439 --> 00:11:16,841
ZOE, I'M SORRY.

157
00:11:16,909 --> 00:11:21,145
YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.

158
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:27,318
LOOK, IT'S BEEN REAL FUN,
BUT WHEN WE
REACH THE NEXT TOWN,

159
00:11:27,387 --> 00:11:30,822
I'LL DROP YOU OFF
WHERE YOU CAN CATCH A BUS.

160
00:11:37,897 --> 00:11:40,064
<i> [ Bell Dings ]</i>

161
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:54,412
FILL HER UP?
YES, PLEASE.

162
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:06,024
CAN I HELP YOU?

163
00:12:06,092 --> 00:12:09,093
YES.
WHEN DOES THE NEXT BUS
COME THROUGH HERE?

164
00:12:09,162 --> 00:12:13,131
OH, UH, HOLD ON A SECOND.
I GOT A SCHEDULE HERE SOMEPLACE.

165
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:24,575
TWENTY-ONE TO DISPATCH.

166
00:12:24,644 --> 00:12:28,245
POSSIBLE ON FEMALE A.P.B.
OUT OF WARRINGTON.
PENNSYLVANIA PLATES.

167
00:12:28,315 --> 00:12:33,117
<i>EDWARD-BAKER-DAVID-6233.</i>

168
00:12:33,186 --> 00:12:36,387
<i>[ Woman On Radio ]</i>
<i>ROGER, 21. SUSPECT WANTED</i>
<i>FOR ASSAULT AND ARMED ROBBERY.</i>

169
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:39,189
<i>APPREHEND WITH CAUTION.</i>

170
00:12:43,129 --> 00:12:46,764
HOWDY, MA'AM.
LICENSE AND REGISTRATION,
PLEASE.

171
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,100
<i>[ Zoe ]</i>
<i>YEAH.</i>

172
00:12:49,169 --> 00:12:53,304
WELL, YOU'VE EITHER GOT
REAL GOOD LUCK OR REAL BAD.

173
00:12:53,372 --> 00:12:57,041
- THE NEXT WESTBOUND DOESN'T GET
HERE TILL 7:45 TONIGHT.
- [ Zoe, Indistinct ]

174
00:12:57,109 --> 00:13:01,546
<i>BUT IF YOU'RE HEADED EASTBOUND,</i>
<i>WELL, HERE COMES</i>
<i>THE 1:30 RIGHT NOW.</i>

175
00:13:04,351 --> 00:13:07,885
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>PRETTY LITTLE THING. I WONDER</i>
<i>WHAT SHE DID TO DESERVE THAT.</i>

176
00:13:09,889 --> 00:13:12,390
-<i> ME TOO.</i>
-<i> [ Car Door Closes ]</i>

177
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:14,959
SO, AM I GONNA
SELL YOU A TICKET?
<i>[ Engine Starts ]</i>

178
00:13:19,232 --> 00:13:22,666
NO. MY PLANS HAVE CHANGED.

179
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:29,474
[ Sighs ]
COME ON.

180
00:13:29,543 --> 00:13:32,910
<i>YOU'RE BEING JERKED AROUND.</i>
<i>I DIDN'T STEAL ANYTHING</i>
<i>FROM ANYONE.</i>

181
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:35,312
MA'AM, WE GOT AN A.P.B.
ON THE POLICE WIRE.

182
00:13:35,382 --> 00:13:38,248
<i> IF IT'S A MISTAKE,</i>
<i> YOU CAN CLEAR IT UP</i>
<i> BACK IN WARRINGTON.</i>

183
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:42,420
I WON'T GET BACK TO WARRINGTON.
HAVEN'T YOU HEARD ANYTHING
I'VE JUST SAID?

184
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:46,424
- YOUR RIDE SHOULD BE HERE
ANY MINUTE.
- IT'S, UH, HERE NOW.

185
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:50,361
JAROD MALLOY, WARRINGTON P.D.
OH, I SEE YOU GOT MY PERP HERE.

186
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:53,564
MALLOY?
I WAS TOLD AN OFFICER HUDONO
WAS COMIN' TO GET HER.

187
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:55,967
OH, YEAH. VINCE.
HE SMACKED INTO...

188
00:13:56,036 --> 00:13:58,202
<i> THE CHIEF'S BRAND NEW LEXUS</i>
<i> ON THE WAY OUT</i>
<i> OF THE PARKING LOT.</i>

189
00:13:58,271 --> 00:14:00,505
OW.
HE'S GONNA BE PATCHIN' UP
HIS BUTT FOR A WHILE,

190
00:14:00,573 --> 00:14:02,573
SO I'M, UH--
I'M COVERIN' FOR HIM.

191
00:14:02,642 --> 00:14:05,609
I JUST WANT TO GO HOME.
YOU GOT YOUR PP-3 FORM?

192
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,712
UH-- UH-- UH--

193
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:10,715
DAMN IT! NO, I MUST HAVE
LEFT IT IN VINCE'S CAR.

194
00:14:10,784 --> 00:14:13,551
WE REALLY CAN'T RELEASE HER
WITHOUT IT.

195
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:16,120
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>

196
00:14:16,189 --> 00:14:19,457
<i>CAN YOU HELP ME OUT HERE?</i>
<i>IT'S MY DAUGHTER'S 10th</i>
<i>BIRTHDAY PARTY TONIGHT.</i>

197
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,526
<i>I REALLY WANT</i>
<i>TO GET BACK IN TIME FOR IT.</i>

198
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:24,962
<i>WHY DON'T YOU LET ME TAKE MY</i>
<i>PERP, AND THEN I'LL FAX YOU</i>
<i>BACK THE PP-3 FORM?</i>

199
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:31,302
<i>[ Car Door Closes ]</i>

200
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:34,571
YEAH, WELL, ALL RIGHT.
I DON'T WANT YOU TO MISS
YOUR DAUGHTER'S PARTY.

201
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:37,008
THANKS.
I OWE YOU ONE.

202
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:44,015
- HEY, WHERE YOU GOIN'?
- I PARKED OUT BACK.

203
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:46,184
<i> [ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>

204
00:14:46,252 --> 00:14:48,820
THAT IS ABSOLUTELY
THE MOST INCREDIBLE THING
ANYONE'S EVER DONE FOR ME.

205
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,921
VINCE IS COMING THROUGH
THE FRONT DOOR.
GET IN THE CAR.

206
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:52,990
YOU HAVE MY CAR, MY MONEY.
YOU COULD HAVE TAKEN EVERYTHING
AND DISAPPEARED.

207
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,092
HOW DID YOU KNOW I WAS TELLING
THE TRUTH ABOUT VINCE?

208
00:14:55,161 --> 00:14:57,862
I COULD'VE MADE THAT STUFF UP.
JAROD!

209
00:14:57,931 --> 00:15:00,531
HOW DID YOU KNOW?
BECAUSE YOU TOLD ME.

210
00:15:07,607 --> 00:15:10,608
YOU'RE A FUGITIVE NOW.
DRIVE, COWBOY!

211
00:15:13,513 --> 00:15:16,380
HEY! HEY, ZOE!

212
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:27,591
JAROD, I THINK IT'S TIME
YOU TELL ME THE TRUTH.

213
00:15:30,362 --> 00:15:36,000
- THE TRUTH ABOUT WHAT?
- YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
NOT A STOCK ANALYST.

214
00:15:36,068 --> 00:15:39,036
YOU MAKE
A PRETTY CONVINCING COP,
BUT THAT'S NOT IT EITHER.

215
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:42,239
SO, WHO ARE YOU REALLY?

216
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:45,609
I'M JUST SOMEONE
WHO'S LOOKING FOR A LITTLE
HAPPILY EVER AFTER MYSELF.

217
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:52,716
I'M SEARCHING FOR MY FAMILY.
I GOT SEPARATED FROM THEM
WHEN I WAS A KID.

218
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:57,421
I'M SEPARATED FROM
MY FAMILY TOO. BY CHOICE.
I RAN AWAY WHEN I WAS 16.

219
00:15:57,490 --> 00:16:00,190
I CAN'T IMAGINE
HAVING A FAMILY AND NOT
WANTING TO BE WITH THEM.

220
00:16:00,259 --> 00:16:02,860
- DON'T YOU MISS THEM?
- MY GRANDMOTHER, I DO A LOT.

221
00:16:02,928 --> 00:16:05,496
SHE'S THE ONLY ONE WHO
EVER REALLY UNDERSTOOD ME.

222
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:08,967
BUT THE OTHERS?
I DON'T REALLY THINK ABOUT THEM.

223
00:16:09,035 --> 00:16:12,470
<i>EXCEPT, OF COURSE,</i>
<i>MY SISTER KATIE.</i>

224
00:16:13,706 --> 00:16:16,507
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING
ABOUT IDENTICAL TWINS.

225
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:19,509
THEY'RE NOT.
KATIE GOT ALL THE BRAINS,

226
00:16:19,578 --> 00:16:21,713
THE TALENT,
THE SENSE OF HUMOR.

227
00:16:21,781 --> 00:16:25,249
NO ONE EVER HAD ANY TROUBLE
TELLING US APART.

228
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:30,521
THERE.
THAT SHOULD KEEP VINCE
OFF OUR BACKS.

229
00:16:30,589 --> 00:16:33,958
<i> THE STATE LINE IS ABOUT</i>
<i> AN HOUR EAST OF HERE.</i>

230
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:36,194
AFTER THAT,
YOU'LL BE FREE AND CLEAR.

231
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:39,530
WE'RE NOT GONNA GO EAST ANYMORE.

232
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,733
A NEW PLAN.
WE'RE GOIN' NORTH.

233
00:16:43,937 --> 00:16:45,870
TO WHERE?
I'M GONNA TEACH YOU...

234
00:16:45,938 --> 00:16:49,206
ABOUT ANOTHER CHILDHOOD STAPLE
I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU MISSED OUT ON.

235
00:16:49,275 --> 00:16:51,208
THE ROAD TRIP.
THE ROAD TRIP?

236
00:16:51,277 --> 00:16:53,878
YEAH. DISTILLED TO
ITS MOST BASIC ESSENCE,

237
00:16:53,947 --> 00:16:55,880
IT IS LOADING UP ON JUNK FOOD,

238
00:16:55,949 --> 00:17:01,018
CRANKIN' THE RADIO AND...
JUST DRIVIN'.

239
00:17:01,087 --> 00:17:04,655
<i>♪ YOU GOT A SMILE SO BRIGHT ♪</i>

240
00:17:04,724 --> 00:17:08,526
<i>♪ YOU KNOW YOU COULD'VE</i>
<i>  BEEN A CANDLE ♪</i>

241
00:17:08,594 --> 00:17:12,363
<i>♪ I'M HOLDING YOU SO TIGHT ♪</i>

242
00:17:12,432 --> 00:17:16,466
<i>♪ YOU KNOW YOU COULD'VE</i>
<i>  BEEN A HANDLE ♪</i>

243
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:20,271
<i>♪ THE WAY YOU SWEPT ME</i>
<i>  OFF MY FEET ♪</i>

244
00:17:20,339 --> 00:17:24,175
<i>♪ YOU KNOW YOU COULD'VE</i>
<i>  BEEN A BROOM ♪</i>

245
00:17:24,244 --> 00:17:28,012
<i>♪ THE WAY YOU SMELL SO SWEET ♪</i>

246
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:31,982
<i>♪ YOU KNOW YOU COULD'VE</i>
<i>  BEEN SOME PERFUME ♪</i>

247
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:36,887
<i>♪ WELL, YOU COULD'VE BEEN</i>
<i>  ANYTHING THAT YOU WANTED TO ♪</i>

248
00:17:36,956 --> 00:17:39,657
<i>♪ AND I CAN TELL ♪</i>

249
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:41,892
<i>♪ THE WAY YOU DO</i>
<i>   THE THINGS YOU DO ♪</i>

250
00:17:41,961 --> 00:17:47,031
<i>♪ THE WAY YOU DO</i>
<i>   THE THINGS YOU DO ♪</i>
<i>♪ OH, YEAH ♪♪</i>

251
00:17:47,099 --> 00:17:49,033
<i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i> OKAY, JOKE'S OVER.</i>

252
00:17:49,101 --> 00:17:51,936
WHAT THE HELL
ARE WE SUPPOSED
TO BE FINDING?

253
00:17:52,004 --> 00:17:55,106
MAYBE JAROD WANTS US TO RUN
LIKE RATS IN A MAZE.

254
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:57,475
OH, YEAH.
OR A FUN HOUSE.

255
00:17:57,544 --> 00:18:00,911
THAT WOULD IMPLY HAVING FUN.
WHAT'S THAT LIGHT DOWN THERE?

256
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:11,456
GREAT. WE GO ON
THE YELLOW BRICK ROAD
DEATH MARCH,

257
00:18:11,524 --> 00:18:13,925
AND ALL WE FIND IS
THIS GOODWILL REJECT?

258
00:18:13,993 --> 00:18:15,993
HEY, THAT'S G.I. JOE.

259
00:18:16,062 --> 00:18:18,329
<i>ONE OF YOUR "DON'T ASK,</i>
<i>DON'T TELL" BUDDIES?</i>

260
00:18:18,398 --> 00:18:20,197
I HAD ONE JUST LIKE THIS
WHEN I WAS A KID.

261
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:23,033
HE HAD THE SAME JUNGLE FATIGUES,
THE SAME FAKE SCAR.

262
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:25,436
OH.
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>WHAT IS IT?</i>

263
00:18:25,505 --> 00:18:28,939
THERE'S A LETTER "B"
CARVED IN THE BOOT.
BUT MINE HAD A "B."

264
00:18:29,008 --> 00:18:30,941
I CARVED IT WITH
KENNY GOLLETTI'S POCKET KNIFE.

265
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:36,113
-<i> [ Sydney ] YOU'RE SAYING</i>
<i> THIS IS YOUR DOLL?</i>
- IT COULDN'T BE.

266
00:18:38,584 --> 00:18:42,887
- COULD IT?
- WE HAVE ENTERED
THE JAROD ZONE.

267
00:18:44,357 --> 00:18:47,892
G.I. JOE
WAS MY BEST FRIEND.

268
00:18:47,961 --> 00:18:50,094
<i>WHEN I WAS 12,</i>
<i>I GOT THE MEASLES.</i>

269
00:18:50,162 --> 00:18:53,798
<i>I SPENT ALL SUMMER</i>
<i>IN THE HOSPITAL.</i>
<i>I ALMOST DIED.</i>

270
00:18:53,867 --> 00:18:55,933
<i>YOU KNOW, NONE OF MY FRIENDS</i>
<i>COULD VISIT ME.</i>

271
00:18:56,002 --> 00:19:00,571
<i>AND THEN MY BROTHER,</i>
<i>HE SNUCK ME IN MY G.I. JOE.</i>

272
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:04,174
<i>AND IT REMINDED ME OF HOME,</i>
<i>OF MY ROOM,</i>

273
00:19:05,945 --> 00:19:09,013
WHERE EVERYTHING
WAS SO MUCH BETTER.

274
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:11,748
YEAH, I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY,

275
00:19:12,951 --> 00:19:16,220
BUT THIS LITTLE GUY
SAVED MY LIFE THAT SUMMER.

276
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:20,724
YOU NEVER MENTIONED THIS STORY
BEFORE, BROOTS.

277
00:19:20,793 --> 00:19:22,727
WELL, I NEVER EVEN
THOUGHT OF IT BEFORE.

278
00:19:24,396 --> 00:19:26,664
- UNTIL--
- TILL JAROD REMINDED YOU.

279
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:45,449
[ Sighs ]
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
TOO ICK?

280
00:19:45,518 --> 00:19:48,685
NOT ICK AT ALL.
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

281
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:52,190
WHY THE CHANGE?
MMM.

282
00:19:52,258 --> 00:19:55,092
WOULD, UH, YOU BE WILLING
TO PRETEND FOR ME AGAIN?

283
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:04,234
OKAY, OKAY.
ANYTIME YOU WANT TO FILL ME IN
ON WHAT'S GOING ON HERE--

284
00:20:09,008 --> 00:20:13,077
ZOE! OH,
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT'S YOU!

285
00:20:13,146 --> 00:20:16,480
HI, GRANDMA.
OH, SWEETIE,
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU!

286
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:20,751
I CAN'T TELL YOU THE TIME I'VE
SPENT WORRYING THAT SOMETHIN'
MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED TO YOU.

287
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,654
SOMETHING HAS HAPPENED TO ME.
THERE'S SOMEONE
I WANT YOU TO MEET.

288
00:20:23,722 --> 00:20:25,656
THIS IS JAROD.
HI.

289
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:28,225
MY HUSBAND.
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE HIM, GRANDMA.
[ Laughing ]

290
00:20:28,293 --> 00:20:31,562
HE'S SWEET AND KIND
AND SPOILS ME ALMOST AS MUCH
AS YOU USED TO.

291
00:20:31,631 --> 00:20:36,333
OH, WELL,
YOU PICKED A PERFECT
TIME TO SURPRISE ME.

292
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,869
YOUR SISTER LINDA
AND HER HUSBAND ARE HERE.

293
00:20:38,938 --> 00:20:41,605
<i> COME ON IN</i>
<i> AND SHARE THE GOOD NEWS.</i>

294
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:45,476
LET'S GO SHARE
THE GOOD NEWS,<i> HONEY.</i>

295
00:20:45,545 --> 00:20:47,744
LINDA, YOU'LL NEVER GUESS
WHO'S HERE.

296
00:20:47,813 --> 00:20:51,615
YOUR BABY SISTER,
AND SHE'S A NEWLYWED.

297
00:20:51,684 --> 00:20:55,919
- HEY, LINDA.
- WOW. WELL, THAT'S... GREAT.

298
00:20:55,988 --> 00:21:00,257
<i> UM, CONGRATULATIONS.</i>

299
00:21:01,861 --> 00:21:04,128
UH-- UH,
LINDA IS MY SISTER.

300
00:21:04,197 --> 00:21:07,364
AND, UH, THIS IS--

301
00:21:10,903 --> 00:21:12,870
THAT'S MY HUSBAND, GREG.

302
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:15,706
<i> ZOE SHOULD KNOW THAT,</i>
<i> BUT SINCE SHE</i>
<i> COULDN'T BE BOTHERED...</i>

303
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:18,609
<i> TO COME TO OUR WEDDING,</i>
<i> THEY'VE NEVER MET.</i>

304
00:21:18,678 --> 00:21:20,911
[ Mouths Word ]

305
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,114
WHO WANTS COFFEE?

306
00:21:26,752 --> 00:21:28,886
<i>[ Linda ]</i>
<i>I'M NOT SURE IF YOU CARE,</i>

307
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:31,622
<i>BUT MOM'S STILL CHAIRING</i>
<i>THE LADIES' GROUP AT THE CLUB,</i>

308
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:34,891
AND, UH, MARK AND HIS WIFE
JUST HAD THEIR
SECOND BOY IN JUNE.

309
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,861
MARK'S OUR BROTHER.
<i> I SWEAR, HE HASN'T HAD</i>
<i> A MINUTE TO REST.</i>

310
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:40,331
<i> HE'S TAKEN OVER</i>
<i> THE FIRM FROM DAD.</i>

311
00:21:40,399 --> 00:21:44,068
IT'S BEEN SUCH A SUCCESS.
THEY MUST HAVE
20 PARTNERS NOW.

312
00:21:44,137 --> 00:21:46,703
- SO, WHAT DO YOU DO, JAROD?
- HMM?

313
00:21:50,476 --> 00:21:53,744
UH, A LITTLE BIT OF THIS,
A LITTLE BIT OF THAT.

314
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:57,848
<i>OH, DON'T BE SO MODEST, HONEY.</i>

315
00:21:57,917 --> 00:22:02,019
JAROD'S AN AEROSPACE ENGINEER.
HE DESIGNS COMMERCIAL JETLINERS.

316
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:06,490
<i> SMALL WORLD.</i>
<i> I RUN THE F.A.A.'S...</i>

317
00:22:06,559 --> 00:22:08,759
<i>PROPULSION RESEARCH FACILITY</i>
<i>IN RED VALLEY.</i>

318
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:11,529
<i> WHAT DO YOU MAKE</i>
<i> OF THESE NEW 6250s</i>
<i> COMIN' OUT OF NORTHUM?</i>

319
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:17,668
WELL, THEY'LL LOOK A LOT BETTER
AFTER THEY SORT OUT THEIR
PREIGNITION WIRE BUS PROBLEMS.

320
00:22:17,737 --> 00:22:21,205
<i>THE S.Q. GYRO PLATFORMS</i>
<i>TEND TO SHIMMY AT HIGH R.P.M.s,</i>

321
00:22:21,273 --> 00:22:23,273
<i>WHICH COULD THROW OFF</i>
<i>THE WHOLE TELEMETRY.</i>

322
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:26,176
- REALLY?
- MM-HMM.

323
00:22:26,245 --> 00:22:28,679
I HADN'T HEARD
ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

324
00:22:28,747 --> 00:22:32,917
-<i> HE'S REALLY SOMETHING.</i>
- YEAH, HE SURE IS.

325
00:22:34,754 --> 00:22:37,554
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A JERK,</i>
<i>AND THIS PROVES IT.</i>

326
00:22:46,498 --> 00:22:48,632
I'M TELLIN' YOU RIGHT NOW,
IF THAT THING STARTS PLAYING...

327
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:51,301
<i>"SOMEWHERE OVER THE RAINBOW,"</i>
<i>I'M GONNA BLOW IT</i>
<i>INTO A MILLION PIECES.</i>

328
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,370
NOW, DON'T. WAIT.

329
00:22:55,241 --> 00:22:57,174
[ Chuckles ]

330
00:22:57,243 --> 00:23:00,077
IT'S A FRENCH SONG
FROM THE EARLY '40s.

331
00:23:00,146 --> 00:23:03,781
-<i> "LES MOTS D'AMOUR."</i>
- "THE LANGUAGE OF LOVE."

332
00:23:03,849 --> 00:23:05,950
IT WAS YOURS, HUH, SYD?

333
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:14,758
<i>♪♪ [ Record ]</i>

334
00:23:14,827 --> 00:23:18,462
WHEN THE ALLIES
LIBERATED OUR CAMP,

335
00:23:18,530 --> 00:23:23,300
<i>MY BROTHER JACOB AND I</i>
<i>HAD TO MAKE OUR WAY</i>
<i>BACK HOME TO LYON.</i>

336
00:23:23,369 --> 00:23:26,537
<i>WHEN WE GOT HOME, THE HOUSE</i>
<i>MY FATHER BUILT BY HAND...</i>
<i>♪♪ [ Woman Singing In French ]</i>

337
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:29,873
<i>WAS REDUCED TO MERE RUBBLE.</i>

338
00:23:31,511 --> 00:23:35,779
BUT IN THE DEBRIS,
WE FOUND THIS RECORD.

339
00:23:35,848 --> 00:23:39,416
<i> IT WAS MY MOTHER'S</i>
<i> FAVORITE SONG.</i>

340
00:23:39,485 --> 00:23:43,620
SHE WOULD PUT IT ON AND MAKE
MY FATHER DANCE WITH HER.

341
00:23:43,689 --> 00:23:47,023
<i> AND MY BROTHER JACOB AND I</i>
<i> WOULD HAVE TO WATCH THEM.</i>

342
00:23:48,293 --> 00:23:51,028
I THOUGHT I HAD
LOST IT YEARS AGO.

343
00:23:51,097 --> 00:23:55,499
SYDNEY, WHAT DO YOU THINK JAROD
IS TRYING TO TELL US
WITH ALL OF THIS?

344
00:23:55,568 --> 00:23:59,570
I DON'T KNOW.
BUT I'M GLAD HE IS.

345
00:23:59,639 --> 00:24:02,139
♪♪ [ Continues ]

346
00:24:10,616 --> 00:24:15,218
<i>FOUR CHILDREN, 12 GRANDCHILDREN</i>
<i>AND 10 GREAT-GRANDKIDS.</i>

347
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:18,288
I'D SAY I'M BLESSED,
WOULDN'T YOU?
I'D SAY.

348
00:24:19,392 --> 00:24:21,458
IS THIS ZOE WITH KATIE?

349
00:24:22,528 --> 00:24:24,561
OH, THIS IS ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

350
00:24:24,629 --> 00:24:28,298
AND THIS WAS TAKEN
JUST A FEW WEEKS
BEFORE, UH, KATIE DIED.

351
00:24:28,367 --> 00:24:31,635
<i>IT WAS ALMOST LIKE THEY BOTH</i>
<i>DIED ON THE SAME DAY.</i>

352
00:24:31,704 --> 00:24:36,406
YOU KNOW, IT HIT
EVERYBODY PRETTY HARD.
BUT ZOE, SHE WAS DEVASTATED.

353
00:24:36,475 --> 00:24:41,144
I CAN IMAGINE.
HER TWIN SISTER.

354
00:24:41,213 --> 00:24:43,580
IN TIME, THE REST OF
THE FAMILY MANAGED TO GO ON.

355
00:24:43,649 --> 00:24:47,251
<i>BUT I THINK SHE RESENTED THEM,</i>
<i>LIKE THEY WERE FORGETTING</i>
<i>ABOUT KATIE.</i>

356
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:51,889
<i>ZOE JUST SORT OF SPIRALED</i>
<i>AFTER THAT, PULLIN' AWAY</i>
<i>FROM THE FAMILY.</i>

357
00:24:51,958 --> 00:24:55,192
- THAT'S WHEN ZOE RAN AWAY.
- MMM.

358
00:24:55,261 --> 00:24:58,328
<i>I HAVE A FEELING</i>
<i>NOW I CAN WORRY LESS.</i>

359
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:06,002
WHAT ARE YOU TWO
GOSSIPING ABOUT?
OH, NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS. SHH.

360
00:25:07,739 --> 00:25:10,240
YOU SLEEP TIGHT.
<i> GOOD NIGHT.</i>

361
00:25:10,309 --> 00:25:13,210
AND I'LL SEE YOU
IN THE MORNING.
[ Chuckles ]

362
00:25:14,579 --> 00:25:17,514
<i> WE DID IT!</i>
<i> WE PULLED IT OFF!</i>
<i> [ Laughs ]</i>

363
00:25:17,583 --> 00:25:19,549
OH, AND, JAROD,
THAT WHOLE AIRLINE ENGINE THING?

364
00:25:19,619 --> 00:25:21,852
PERFECT.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

365
00:25:21,921 --> 00:25:24,588
WHY IS IT SO IMPORTANT
THAT THEY THINK YOUR LIFE
IS SOMETHING THAT IT'S NOT?

366
00:25:24,657 --> 00:25:27,992
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
THE FAMILY SCREWUP.

367
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:30,727
NO DIRECTION,
NO DECENT JOB.

368
00:25:30,796 --> 00:25:33,664
LOUSY RELATIONSHIPS.

369
00:25:33,732 --> 00:25:37,067
LOOK AT MY BROTHERS AND SISTERS.
ALL SUCCESS STORIES.

370
00:25:37,135 --> 00:25:39,837
WELL, WHO CARES
WHAT THEY THINK?
I DON'T.

371
00:25:39,905 --> 00:25:41,905
BUT MY GRANDMOTHER--
I WANT HER TO THINK THAT...

372
00:25:41,974 --> 00:25:45,976
I'VE TURNED MY LIFE AROUND--
THAT I'M HAPPY.

373
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:48,912
EVEN IF IT IS A LIE.
IT'LL BE EASIER FOR HER
THAT WAY.

374
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:54,551
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?
NOTHING.

375
00:25:57,723 --> 00:26:02,459
HEY, I KNOW HOW WE CAN REALLY
CONVINCE THEM THAT
WE'RE NEWLYWEDS.

376
00:26:03,829 --> 00:26:05,996
[ Meows ]

377
00:26:07,199 --> 00:26:09,332
STICK AROUND.

378
00:26:37,229 --> 00:26:40,965
- WHAT IS IT?
- HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN
YOU WERE SICK?

379
00:26:54,646 --> 00:26:57,314
-<i> HOW'D YOU KNOW I WAS SICK?</i>
-<i> THESE PRESCRIPTIONS...</i>

380
00:26:57,383 --> 00:26:59,983
ARE ALL PRECURSORS
FOR CHEMOTHERAPY.

381
00:27:00,052 --> 00:27:02,385
HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN?

382
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:07,224
I DON'T KNOW.
THREE WEEKS.

383
00:27:07,293 --> 00:27:11,795
AND YOU HAVEN'T FILLED
THE PRESCRIPTIONS YET. ZOE--

384
00:27:11,864 --> 00:27:14,798
- I HAVEN'T GOTTEN AROUND TO IT.
- THIS IS SERIOUS.

385
00:27:14,867 --> 00:27:17,100
YOUR CAREFREE ATTITUDE
WON'T MAKE IT GO AWAY.

386
00:27:17,169 --> 00:27:19,769
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME,
SOME SCENE OUT OF<i> LOVE STORY?</i>

387
00:27:19,838 --> 00:27:21,838
SORRY.
DRAMA QUEEN'S NOT MY STYLE.

388
00:27:21,907 --> 00:27:24,575
I'M GOING TO
THE DRUGSTORE TOMORROW.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

389
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:27,377
I WANT TO.
I DON'T WANT YOU TO.

390
00:27:30,416 --> 00:27:33,183
JAROD, I'VE SEEN PEOPLE FIGHT
THIS TYPE OF CANCER BEFORE.

391
00:27:33,252 --> 00:27:37,621
<i> ALL THE AGONY AND SICKNESS.</i>
<i> THE CURE'S WORSE</i>
<i> THAN THE DISEASE.</i>

392
00:27:37,690 --> 00:27:41,992
- BESIDES, MOST OF THEM
DIE ANYWAY.
- THERE ARE NEW TREATMENTS--

393
00:27:42,061 --> 00:27:44,961
<i>ADVANCEMENTS THAT COULD</i>
<i>GIVE YOU A REAL CHANCE.</i>

394
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:48,798
- SO NOW YOU'RE A DOCTOR TOO?
- I'M JUST SAYING IT DOESN'T
HAVE TO BE A FATAL CONDITION.

395
00:27:48,867 --> 00:27:51,134
LIFE IS A FATAL CONDITION.

396
00:27:54,573 --> 00:27:57,207
YOU GET OFF THE BUS,
SUCK ALL THE JUICE OUT
OF THE YEARS YOU HAVE,

397
00:27:57,276 --> 00:28:00,778
AND IT'S...
GOOD NIGHT, CLEVELAND.

398
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:03,447
YOU'VE BEEN A BEAUTIFUL CROWD.
THOSE ARE THE RULES.

399
00:28:03,516 --> 00:28:05,649
<i> ALWAYS HAVE BEEN.</i>
<i> I GET IT.</i>

400
00:28:05,718 --> 00:28:09,686
AND I'M NOT GONNA CRY AND PLEAD
FOR SPECIAL TREATMENT
JUST AS THE CURTAIN'S CLOSING.

401
00:28:09,755 --> 00:28:13,490
<i> YOU KNOW, IT'S WEIRD,</i>
<i> BUT IN SOME WAYS,</i>
<i> IT'S BEEN A GOOD THING.</i>

402
00:28:13,558 --> 00:28:16,059
<i> IT MADE ME REALIZE I HAD TO</i>
<i> GET AWAY FROM VINCE.</i>

403
00:28:16,128 --> 00:28:18,862
BROUGHT ME HERE TO SEE
MY GRANDMOTHER AGAIN.

404
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:20,964
EVEN BROUGHT ME TO YOU.

405
00:28:25,904 --> 00:28:27,904
YOU CAN'T GIVE UP
WITHOUT A FIGHT.

406
00:28:29,774 --> 00:28:32,976
YES, I CAN.
JAROD, DON'T SAY ANYTHING...

407
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:35,512
ABOUT THIS TO ANYONE,
ESPECIALLY MY GRANDMOTHER.

408
00:28:35,581 --> 00:28:38,147
ZOE--
PROMISE ME?

409
00:28:40,885 --> 00:28:45,756
- [ Scoffs ]
I CAN'T ACCEPT THIS.
- YOU HAVE TO. THIS IS MY LIFE.

410
00:28:45,825 --> 00:28:48,524
THESE ARE MY DECISIONS.

411
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:51,628
BESIDES, MAYBE I DESERVE IT.

412
00:28:53,799 --> 00:28:55,832
JAROD?

413
00:29:13,252 --> 00:29:16,286
I VOTE WE GO BACK
TO THE MUNCHKIN AND SHOOT
OUR WAY OUT OF THIS MADHOUSE.

414
00:29:16,355 --> 00:29:20,223
THIS JOURNEY ISN'T OVER
TILL WE FIND WHAT JAROD
LEFT FOR YOU, MISS PARKER.

415
00:29:20,292 --> 00:29:22,526
<i>AND I THINK</i>
<i>WE JUST FOUND IT.</i>

416
00:29:22,595 --> 00:29:25,061
THIS LOOKS LIKE THE BASKET
THAT DOROTHY CARRIED TOTO IN.

417
00:29:25,131 --> 00:29:28,364
WELL, IF JAROD RUSTLED UP
MY OLD DOG MR. SHECKLE,

418
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:30,434
IT AIN'T GONNA BE PRETTY.

419
00:29:37,375 --> 00:29:41,744
- A THIMBLE?
-<i> [ Broots ] MISS PARKER?</i>

420
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:46,015
MY FAMILY...

421
00:29:46,084 --> 00:29:48,885
DIDN'T SPEND A LOT OF TIME
TOGETHER WHEN I WAS GROWING UP.

422
00:29:48,953 --> 00:29:53,456
<i> MY FATHER WAS ALWAYS</i>
<i> AT THE CENTRE.</i>

423
00:29:53,525 --> 00:29:56,727
IF HE WAS AROUND,
MY MOTHER WAS OFF
IN AN ORPHANAGE SOMEWHERE.

424
00:29:56,796 --> 00:29:59,028
BUT ONE DAY,

425
00:30:00,232 --> 00:30:02,165
<i>THERE HAD BEEN A BIG STORM.</i>

426
00:30:02,234 --> 00:30:04,434
<i>BUT THE ROADS WERE ALL CLOSED.</i>

427
00:30:04,502 --> 00:30:07,137
<i>EVERYTHING WAS SHUT DOWN.</i>

428
00:30:07,206 --> 00:30:11,007
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>
<i>DADDY, OF COURSE, WAS ANNOYED.</i>

429
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:14,477
<i>BUT I WAS ELATED,</i>
<i>BECAUSE IT WAS</i>
<i>JUST THE THREE OF US...</i>

430
00:30:14,546 --> 00:30:18,548
<i>TRAPPED TOGETHER</i>
<i>IN THE HOUSE.</i>

431
00:30:21,686 --> 00:30:25,989
<i> SO, YOU ALL JUST</i>
<i> SEWED SOMETHING.</i>

432
00:30:30,729 --> 00:30:32,829
<i>[ Chuckling ]</i>

433
00:30:34,366 --> 00:30:36,032
[ Chuckling ]

434
00:30:36,101 --> 00:30:39,936
- WE PLAYED MONOPOLY.
- OH.

435
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:42,773
WE PLAYED MONOPOLY ALL DAY
AND INTO THE NIGHT.

436
00:30:42,842 --> 00:30:48,311
<i> DADDY WAS THE SHOE,</i>
<i> MY MOTHER WAS THE CAR,</i>
<i> AND I WAS...</i>

437
00:30:51,082 --> 00:30:53,016
THE THIMBLE.

438
00:30:53,084 --> 00:30:56,753
<i> [ Clears Throat ]</i>
<i> SO, WHY DO YOU SUPPOSE</i>
<i> JAROD IS DOING THIS?</i>

439
00:30:56,822 --> 00:30:59,556
<i> I MEAN, WHAT DO YOU--</i>
<i> WHAT DO YOU THINK</i>
<i> HE'S TRYING TO SAY?</i>

440
00:30:59,625 --> 00:31:04,193
- THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME.
- THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME.

441
00:31:04,262 --> 00:31:07,664
<i> WHICH IS HOW WE GET</i>
<i> THE HELL OUT OF HERE.</i>

442
00:31:10,136 --> 00:31:14,871
- THERE'S NO PLACE--
- WE'VE SAID IT
THREE TIMES ALREADY!

443
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:17,141
I KNOW, BUT I GOTTA HEAR IT
WITH THE SHOES CLICKING.

444
00:31:17,209 --> 00:31:21,377
YOU'RE GONNA HEAR IT
WITH THE CLICKING
OF MY .9 MILLIMETER...

445
00:31:21,446 --> 00:31:24,515
<i> IF YOU DON'T OPEN</i>
<i> THE DAMN DOOR!</i>

446
00:31:26,485 --> 00:31:28,418
<i> [ Lock Clicking ]</i>

447
00:31:31,156 --> 00:31:33,690
HEY, NICE ATTITUDE!
DON'T FORGET TO COME BACK...

448
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:36,660
AND SEE ME NEXT TIME
YOU'RE IN THE EMERALD CITY, HUH?

449
00:31:38,731 --> 00:31:42,866
-<i> I REALLY WISH YOU</i>
<i> WEREN'T LEAVIN' SO SOON.</i>
- SO DO I.

450
00:31:42,935 --> 00:31:44,935
BUT JAROD'S SPEAKING AT
A BIG CONFERENCE UP NORTH.

451
00:31:45,004 --> 00:31:47,571
AND IF WE DON'T LEAVE NOW,
WELL, HE'S GONNA BE LATE.

452
00:31:47,639 --> 00:31:50,707
<i> WELL, DON'T YOU KEEP</i>
<i> MY LITTLE GIRL</i>
<i> AWAY TOO LONG, JAROD.</i>

453
00:31:50,776 --> 00:31:53,009
I WANT TO SEE HER
BACK HERE SOON.

454
00:31:56,448 --> 00:31:58,448
OH, SHE'LL BE BACK
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

455
00:32:05,291 --> 00:32:07,891
OH, ONE MORE THING, GRAM.
I HAVE SOMETHING FOR YOU.

456
00:32:07,959 --> 00:32:10,227
A, UH-- A SURPRISE
BIRTHDAY PRESENT.

457
00:32:10,296 --> 00:32:14,798
- BUT MY BIRTHDAY
ISN'T FOR TWO MONTHS.
- THAT'S WHY IT'S A SURPRISE.

458
00:32:14,867 --> 00:32:17,768
<i>BUT DON'T OPEN IT</i>
<i>UNTIL AFTER WE LEAVE.</i>

459
00:32:17,837 --> 00:32:20,771
I LOVE YOU.
I LOVE YOU, ZOE.

460
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,806
OH, I LOVE YOU.
[ Grunts ]

461
00:32:24,843 --> 00:32:26,844
BYE.

462
00:32:34,152 --> 00:32:36,954
THANK YOU, JAROD,
FOR KEEPING YOUR PROMISE.

463
00:32:37,023 --> 00:32:39,723
I STILL THINK
YOU SHOULD TELL HER.

464
00:32:39,792 --> 00:32:41,825
BETTER SHE REMEMBER ME
LIKE THIS.

465
00:32:41,894 --> 00:32:44,295
DRIVING AWAY ONE LAST TIME?

466
00:32:44,363 --> 00:32:49,232
NO. HAPPY.

467
00:32:52,471 --> 00:32:56,206
AND I'D REALLY APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU'D BE HAPPY TOO.

468
00:32:56,275 --> 00:32:58,842
YOU KNOW,
ENOUGH OF THIS MOROSE CRAP.

469
00:32:58,911 --> 00:33:01,812
I PLAN ON MAKING THE MOST
OF MY TIME THAT'S LEFT.

470
00:33:04,082 --> 00:33:06,316
<i>[ Man On Radio ]</i>
<i>AND BY THE WAY, IF YOU'RE</i>
<i>OUT NEAR FREEBURG TODAY,</i>

471
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:08,418
<i> THE LOCAL "Y"</i>
<i> IS PUTTING ON A CARNIVAL.</i>

472
00:33:08,487 --> 00:33:11,288
<i>THEY'RE GONNA HAVE GAMES, RIDES.</i>
<i>BRING THE WHOLE FAMILY DOWN.</i>
COME ON, JAROD.

473
00:33:11,357 --> 00:33:13,523
<i>SHOW ME A GOOD TIME.</i>
<i>[ Radio ]</i>
<i>YOU'LL HAVE LOTS OF FUN--</i>

474
00:33:13,592 --> 00:33:15,525
<i>[ Door Opening ]</i>

475
00:33:15,594 --> 00:33:18,695
IT'S NOT HOME,
BUT IT'LL DO.

476
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:23,400
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>LOOKS LIKE THE NEXT PIECE OF</i>
<i>JAROD'S PUZZLE'S ALREADY HERE.</i>

477
00:33:23,469 --> 00:33:25,402
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>THE WICKED WITCH OF THE WEST.</i>

478
00:33:25,471 --> 00:33:29,940
<i> HEY, DOESN'T IT KIND OF</i>
<i> LOOK A LITTLE... LIKE--</i>

479
00:33:31,010 --> 00:33:34,310
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A COMPLIMENT.

480
00:33:34,379 --> 00:33:37,948
<i> THERE MUST BE MORE THAN</i>
<i> THE OBVIOUS INTERPRETATION.</i>

481
00:33:38,017 --> 00:33:40,617
MAYBE SOME DEEPER MEANING?

482
00:33:40,686 --> 00:33:43,186
HMM?

483
00:33:43,255 --> 00:33:46,156
[ Evil Laughter,
Sizzling ]

484
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:50,160
[ Laughter Continues ]

485
00:33:53,498 --> 00:33:56,500
[ Warped Laughter ]

486
00:33:56,569 --> 00:33:59,202
[ Laughter Stops ]

487
00:33:59,271 --> 00:34:01,571
HEY, LOOK.

488
00:34:05,944 --> 00:34:09,113
BROOTS, CALL THE AIRSTRIP.
TELL THEM TO GET
MY BROOMSTICK FIRED UP.

489
00:34:09,181 --> 00:34:11,348
WE'RE GOIN' BACK TO KANSAS.

490
00:34:15,721 --> 00:34:17,821
<i>[ Zoe ] THE MANAGER SAID</i>
<i>OUR ROOM IS AROUND HERE.</i>

491
00:34:20,392 --> 00:34:22,392
YOU'RE AMAZING, JAROD.
I'VE NEVER SEEN SOMEONE...

492
00:34:22,461 --> 00:34:24,895
WIN ONE GAME
AFTER ANOTHER LIKE THAT.

493
00:34:24,963 --> 00:34:28,532
IT'S REALLY VERY SIMPLE.
IT'S ALL A MATTER OF GEOMETRY
AND PHYSICS.

494
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:31,902
RIGHT.
OKAY, I WORKED A STINT
AS A CARNY A WHILE BACK.

495
00:34:31,970 --> 00:34:34,871
I KNOW ALL THEIR SECRETS.
NOW, WHY DOESN'T THAT
SURPRISE ME?

496
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:37,307
[ Both Chuckling ]

497
00:34:37,376 --> 00:34:40,143
HE GAVE US
LUCKY NUMBER SEVEN.

498
00:34:47,787 --> 00:34:50,287
WHERE ARE YOU GOING NOW?

499
00:34:53,626 --> 00:34:57,060
ZOE?
IT'S MAGICAL, JAROD.

500
00:34:57,129 --> 00:34:59,730
DON'T YOU FEEL
LIKE TAKIN' A DIP?

501
00:34:59,798 --> 00:35:02,298
COME ON.
ZOE, NO.

502
00:35:02,367 --> 00:35:05,269
JAROD, YES.
LOOK AT IT.
IT'S CALLING US.

503
00:35:05,337 --> 00:35:07,771
I DON'T HAVE
A BATHING SUIT.
NEITHER DO I.

504
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:11,241
I DON'T KNOW.
HEY, I PAID FOR THE ROOM.

505
00:35:11,310 --> 00:35:13,910
THE LEAST YOU CAN DO
IS SWIM WITH ME.
[ Sighs ]

506
00:35:13,979 --> 00:35:16,146
YOU'VE NEVER SKINNY-DIPPED
BEFORE, HAVE YOU?

507
00:35:16,214 --> 00:35:18,148
IS-- IS THAT
WHAT THEY CALL IT?

508
00:35:18,217 --> 00:35:20,951
YEAH. JUMP IN
AND I'LL SHOW YOU WHY.

509
00:35:24,823 --> 00:35:28,558
- YOU'RE CRAZY, YOU KNOW THAT?
- AND YOU'RE STALLING.

510
00:35:28,627 --> 00:35:31,561
<i>JUST WHAT DOES A NAKED WOMAN</i>
<i>HAVE TO DO TO GET YOU IN HERE?</i>

511
00:35:34,566 --> 00:35:36,500
<i>[ Splashing ]</i>

512
00:35:41,073 --> 00:35:44,774
IT'S NOT SO BAD, IS IT?
NICE.

513
00:35:44,843 --> 00:35:47,077
IT'S PRETTY GOOD.

514
00:35:57,289 --> 00:35:59,223
HI.

515
00:35:59,291 --> 00:36:01,225
HI.

516
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:49,673
MMM. ZOE?

517
00:36:52,544 --> 00:36:57,648
- [ Chuckles ]
OKAY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- LAST NIGHT WAS AMAZING.

518
00:36:57,716 --> 00:37:00,850
- MMM.
- THE LAST 48 HOURS
HAVE BEEN AMAZING.

519
00:37:10,763 --> 00:37:13,563
FALLING IN LOVE
WASN'T PART OF THE PLAN.

520
00:37:13,632 --> 00:37:18,835
- WHAT PLAN?
- THE ONE THAT SAYS I HAVE TO GO
NOW, AND IT HAS TO BE ALONE.

521
00:37:18,904 --> 00:37:21,871
WHAT? WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

522
00:37:21,940 --> 00:37:24,574
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.
UNLOCK THESE CUFFS.

523
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:27,610
- UNLOCK THE CUFFS!
GIVE ME THE KEY!
- I CAN'T.

524
00:37:27,679 --> 00:37:29,879
<i>LOOK, YOU'RE GOING</i>
<i>TO GET WELL.</i>
<i>YOU'LL BEAT THIS!</i>

525
00:37:29,948 --> 00:37:32,749
NO, I WON'T!
I'M SURE OF THAT.

526
00:37:32,818 --> 00:37:35,351
I NEED TO END THINGS MY WAY.
GO OUT WITH A BANG, RIGHT?

527
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:38,555
- ZOE, DON'T DO THIS.
- JAROD, YOU'RE GOOD
AT PRETENDING.

528
00:37:38,624 --> 00:37:41,624
- JUST PRETEND YOU NEVER MET ME.
- ZOE! ZOE--

529
00:37:41,693 --> 00:37:45,762
-<i> ZOE!</i>
-<i> [ Door Closes ]</i>

530
00:37:52,871 --> 00:37:55,105
[ Grunting ]

531
00:37:57,142 --> 00:38:00,276
HI, HONEY.
GOIN' SOMEWHERE?

532
00:38:06,085 --> 00:38:08,985
-<i> THE GAME'S OVER.</i>
<i>  IT'S TIME TO GO HOME.</i>
- THAT'S NOT MY HOME ANYMORE.

533
00:38:09,054 --> 00:38:11,721
I TOLD YOU, YOU AND I ARE OVER.
IF YOU DIDN'T WANT ME
TO FIND YOU,

534
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:14,925
THEN YOU WOULDN'T HAVE
USED YOUR CREDIT CARD
TO RENT THE ROOM.

535
00:38:14,993 --> 00:38:17,394
YOU HAVEN'T BLOWN
ALL THAT MONEY?
THE MONEY WAS MINE!

536
00:38:17,463 --> 00:38:19,496
IT WAS OURS!
FINE. YOU KNOW WHAT?

537
00:38:19,565 --> 00:38:23,500
YOU CAN HAVE IT,
BUT YOU CAN'T HAVE ME!
YOU REALLY WANNA TAKE ME ON?

538
00:38:23,569 --> 00:38:25,635
<i> DO YOU?</i>
I WILL IF I HAVE TO.

539
00:38:25,704 --> 00:38:28,238
WHAT THE HELL?
YOU'RE WITH THIS GUY?
COME ON, ZOE. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

540
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:30,941
HEY!
LOOK, SHE DOESN'T WANNA
BE WITH YOU.

541
00:38:31,010 --> 00:38:33,076
WHY CAN'T YOU GET THAT
THROUGH YOUR HEAD?
THAT'S NOT HER DECISION.

542
00:38:33,145 --> 00:38:35,178
AND IT'S NOT YOURS EITHER.
LET'S GO.

543
00:38:35,247 --> 00:38:38,681
OH, MY GOD, VINCE, NO!
YOU MUST'VE HAD SOME FUN
LAST NIGHT, HUH?

544
00:38:38,750 --> 00:38:41,851
<i>I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.</i>
<i>NOT LIKE THE FUN YOU AND I</i>
<i>ARE GONNA HAVE TONIGHT.</i>

545
00:38:42,887 --> 00:38:46,522
[ Grunting ]

546
00:38:46,591 --> 00:38:48,758
VINCE, DON'T!

547
00:38:53,732 --> 00:38:56,366
SON OF A BITCH!

548
00:38:58,236 --> 00:39:00,871
YOU GOT SOME BRASS ONES!
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT!

549
00:39:08,513 --> 00:39:10,680
[ Engine Starts ]

550
00:39:11,783 --> 00:39:14,951
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>
ZOE! ZOE!

551
00:39:38,944 --> 00:39:41,544
<i> ZOE?</i>

552
00:39:43,148 --> 00:39:45,148
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

553
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:48,884
I CALLED YOUR GRANDMOTHER.
SHE SAID THIS IS WHERE
YOUR SISTER DIED.

554
00:39:51,390 --> 00:39:54,891
- PLEASE, I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.
- OH, NO, YOU DON'T.

555
00:39:56,728 --> 00:39:59,496
YOU WANT TO STOP ME
FROM FINISHING MY JOURNEY.

556
00:40:02,968 --> 00:40:07,771
ZOE, WHAT HAPPENED WAS TERRIBLE,
AND IT WAS VERY SAD,

557
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:10,373
BUT IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

558
00:40:10,442 --> 00:40:13,276
YOU HAVE TO STOP
BLAMING YOURSELF FOR IT.

559
00:40:13,345 --> 00:40:16,512
I'M THE ONE WHO TOLD HER
TO CLIMB UP HERE.

560
00:40:16,581 --> 00:40:19,782
I ONLY MEANT IT AS A JOKE,
BUT KATIE,
SHE NEVER TURNED DOWN A DARE.

561
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,621
SHE WAS RIGHT ABOUT HERE
WHEN SHE SLIPPED.

562
00:40:26,824 --> 00:40:31,060
KATIE SHOULD HAVE BEEN
THE ONE THAT LIVED.
SHE WAS SMARTER, FUNNIER.

563
00:40:31,129 --> 00:40:35,198
SO YOU THINK
YOU DESERVE TO DIE.
IS THAT IT?

564
00:40:36,568 --> 00:40:38,701
IT'S NOT LIKE I'VE BEEN
A BIG SUCCESS IN LIFE.

565
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:40,903
LOOK AT WHAT I'VE DONE TO MINE.
I'VE MADE A MESS OF IT.

566
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:43,874
BECAUSE YOU'VE BEEN PUNISHING
YOURSELF FOR WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR SISTER,

567
00:40:43,942 --> 00:40:48,111
<i> AND THAT'S WHY YOU'RE</i>
<i> NOT FIGHTING THE CANCER.</i>

568
00:40:48,180 --> 00:40:50,980
THIS ISN'T ABOUT LIVING LIFE
TO THE FULLEST...

569
00:40:51,049 --> 00:40:53,683
OR GOING OUT WITH A BANG.

570
00:40:53,752 --> 00:40:57,821
YOU'RE NOT FIGHTING IT
BECAUSE YOU DON'T THINK
YOU DESERVE TO BEAT IT.

571
00:40:57,889 --> 00:40:59,890
GOD, JAROD.

572
00:41:02,027 --> 00:41:04,994
I'M JUST SO SCARED.
I KNOW YOU ARE.

573
00:41:05,063 --> 00:41:07,297
AND I'M GOING TO HELP YOU.

574
00:41:07,365 --> 00:41:09,466
BUT THERE'S ONLY
ONE PLACE TO DO IT,

575
00:41:10,502 --> 00:41:12,635
AND THAT'S WITH
THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE.

576
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:17,974
WHY WOULD JAROD BRING US
ALL THE WAY BACK HERE...

577
00:41:18,043 --> 00:41:21,111
WHEN NOTHING HAS CHANGED?

578
00:41:21,179 --> 00:41:25,448
WELL, NOTHING EXCEPT THIS.
IT'S NOT EXACTLY RUBY SLIPPERS.

579
00:41:25,517 --> 00:41:29,819
I THINK JAROD FELL ASLEEP
IN THE MAGICAL POPPIES
A LITTLE TOO LONG.

580
00:41:29,888 --> 00:41:32,989
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>A NOTE FROM JAROD, SYDNEY?</i>
<i>WHAT DOES IT SAY?</i>

581
00:41:36,061 --> 00:41:39,629
"THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME."
IN CASE WE DIDN'T
GET IT BEFORE?

582
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:42,565
"EVERYONE DESERVES ONE.
SO WHY DON'T YOU...

583
00:41:42,634 --> 00:41:46,235
LEAVE ME ALONE
AND LET ME FIND MINE?"

584
00:41:55,113 --> 00:41:58,181
[ Kid Laughing, Chattering ]

585
00:41:58,250 --> 00:42:01,685
HEY-HEY-HEY!
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

586
00:42:01,753 --> 00:42:03,753
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

587
00:42:03,822 --> 00:42:09,359
YEAH, I'M SURE.
YOU GOT A LONG FIGHT
AHEAD OF YOU.

588
00:42:09,427 --> 00:42:12,061
I DON'T WANT YOU TO HAVE TO
GO THROUGH IT ALONE.

589
00:42:12,130 --> 00:42:15,364
I'M NOT ALONE.
I'VE GOT THEM.

590
00:42:17,402 --> 00:42:19,335
AND I'VE GOT YOU.

591
00:42:21,740 --> 00:42:25,341
IN HERE.
I WANT TO STAY WITH YOU.

592
00:42:26,445 --> 00:42:30,046
I KNOW.
BUT YOU CAN'T STAY, CAN YOU?

593
00:42:32,117 --> 00:42:34,918
I CAN SEE IT IN YOUR EYES.

594
00:42:41,959 --> 00:42:46,262
THANK YOU...
FOR HELPING ME
FIND MY WAY BACK HOME.

595
00:42:47,265 --> 00:42:49,733
GOOD-BYE.

596
00:42:51,236 --> 00:42:53,235
YOU EVER SAY THAT WORD AGAIN,
I'LL KICK YOUR BUTT.

597
00:42:53,304 --> 00:42:57,006
OKAY.
GO.

